criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age > 18 years old;

          -  acceptance of written informed consent to undergo an endoscopic bariatric therapy;

          -  I and II grade obesity: BMI 30-34.99 with many failed attempts at noninvasive weight
             loss and with obesity-related diseases; BMI 35-39.99 with many failed attempts at
             noninvasive weight loss.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  coagulation problems (such as platelet < 30000, INR >1.8), chronic kidney disease,
             heart disease;

          -  any other contraindication for endoscopic bariatric procedure;

          -  patients who do not give their consent to the enrollment in the study or are
             incompetent, unconscious or unable to express their consent for any reason;

          -  patients suffering from any condition which precludes compliance with study
             instructions;

          -  patient has any allergy or other known contraindication or intolerance to the
             medications used in the study for the preparation;

          -  women who are either pregnant or nursing at the time of screening, or are of
             child-bearing potential and do not practice acceptable methods of contraception;

          -  patient suffers from a life threatening condition.
